* Use Ctrl+ Shift + r  === To reload the page.

* Now react have two kind of components class based components and functions based components. Nowadays function based components are in trend because they are easy to understand less complex. That's why react also shifted from class to function based components.


* JSX - Javascript Syntax Extension is what we written in the           funstion APP () { return(JSX) }. It is much like HTML with some changes like 
  for-> htmlFor 
  tab-> tabIndex 
  class-> className

* We can also write JS in JSX by using curly brackets {}.

* In react while using JSX we can return only one tag, like div by default. We can include other tags into it or we can also use JSX fragments which is " <>   </>". 

* We can also open the react app in our phone from the ip address given to us if phone and laptop are connected over same wifi

* In react we return jsx by using paranteses  return( JSX ) because JS automatically add semicolon in each line. To avoid it we use ().







